Aegon, Anheuser-Busch InBev, Bekaert: Benelux Equity Preview

-- B y   M a u d   v a n   G a a l   a n d   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-08-11T04:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/aegon-anheuser-busch-inbev-bekaert-benelux-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Benelux markets. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are from the previous close.  The  AEX-Index (AEX)  in Amsterdam declined 3.4 percent to 277.27.
 Belgium ’s Bel20 Index lost 2.9 percent to 2,091.74. Luxembourg’s
LuxX Index retreated 2.9 percent to 1,117.33.  Dutch stocks:  Aegon NV (AGN)  : The Dutch owner of U.S. insurer
Transamerica Corp. may report second-quarter net income of 339
million euros ($481 million), according to the average estimate
of 15 analysts in a Bloomberg survey. Aegon shares slid 6.2
percent to 2.97 euros.  Belgian stocks:  Anheuser-Busch InBev NV (ABI)  : The world’s biggest
brewer may report second-quarter profit excluding some items of
98 cents a share, according to the average of 15 analyst
estimates compiled by Bloomberg. AB InBev shares sank 4 percent
to 35.15 euros.  Bekaert NV (BEKB BB): The world’s largest maker of steel
cord used in tires agreed to sell its specialty-films business
to a unit of Cie. de Saint-Gobain SA. Bekaert said the
transaction will reduce net debt by about 80 million euros and
result in a gain of about 10 million euros. Bekaert shares
dropped 2.4 percent to 36.22 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
